# UI / Design system

Single locked theme **"Suar Dermaga" (Ombak v2 — harbor light over the ledger)**: the warm-paper
"Ledger on Paper" base kept verbatim (hairline structure, borders over shadows, teal accent,
Plus Jakarta Sans + Geist Mono), evolved with a **sea-glass horizon wash**, a **navy "hull at
dusk" sidebar** (hue locked ≤252 — never purple), an amber **suar/beacon** attention system, and
the **Pandu** assistant pattern. Tokens (OKLCH) live in `apps/web/src/styles/globals.css` —
light + dark via `next-themes`. Change the accent only via `--primary`/`--ring`/`--sidebar-*`.

**Suar Dermaga specifics (on top of Ledger on Paper):**

- **`--sea-glass`** is the ONLY "water" fill: the dashboard `horizon-wash` utility (shell `<main>`
  only; cards stay pure white) and Pandu surfaces. Never a card/table background.
- **Split neutrals stay**: `--secondary`/`--muted`/`--accent` distinct; `--border` ≠ `--input`.
- **Signed numerics**: `--signed-up`/`--signed-down` via **`NumberDelta`**; losses/negative
  margins use `text-signed-down`, NEVER `text-destructive` (destructive = app failure only).
- **Status colors come ONLY from `StatusBadge`/`STATUS_BADGE_TONES`** (`components/status-badge.tsx`):
  tones ok/info/warn/urgent/danger/neutral over `--status-ok/info/warn`, `--highlight(+-strong)`,
  `--destructive`. No raw Tailwind palette (emerald/amber/sky/rose) for status — dark mode comes
  free from tokens. Warn callout trio: `border-highlight/40 bg-highlight/15 text-status-warn`;
  ok trio: `border-status-ok/30 bg-status-ok/10 text-status-ok`. Exception: permanent dark camera
  surfaces (mobile scanner overlay, video stage) may keep their raw dark-surface colors.
- **`num`** (mono+tabular) on EVERY number/code the user reads — stock, money, qty, resi, SKU
  codes, counts. **`num-display`** (mono 28px w700) = hero numerals (StatCard value, POS total).
- **`eyebrow`** micro-caps for section/stat/nav labels (never paired with another `text-*` size).
- **Elevation = hairline**: no shadows on cards; shadows only on true overlays.
- **Motion**: `--ease-tide` for entrances/dock; skeleton = `shimmer-water` (not pulse); a GLOBAL
  `prefers-reduced-motion` guard lives in globals.css; JS-driven motion (recharts) must also gate
  via **`useReducedMotion`** → `isAnimationActive={!reducedMotion}`.
- **Maritime budget**: `WaveHairline` (riak divider) ONLY at hero/landing/auth section breaks;
  `LighthouseArt` + "Suar" voice only on error/404 routes; maritime words appear as eyebrows
  ("Anjungan") — primary nav labels stay functional. Tables/badges/forms are motif-free.

## Brand chrome

- **`BrandMark`/`BrandBadge`** (`components/brand-mark.tsx`) — the falcon-eye-over-riak mark; the
  ONLY brand mark (never an inline letter chip). Favicon `app/icon.svg`, `apple-icon.tsx`,
  `opengraph-image.tsx` (+ data-free variant for `/share/[token]` — resi must never leak into
  link previews), `manifest.ts`, `robots.ts`, `<html lang="id">`, `metadataBase` from
  `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL`, viewport themeColor pair.
- **Branded failure routes**: `app/not-found.tsx`, `app/error.tsx`, `app/global-error.tsx`,
  `app/(dashboard)/error.tsx` (keeps the shell frame), route `loading.tsx` (incl. the share
  page). Calm "Suar" voice + lighthouse art + a way back. Never ship a route that can fall
  through to an unbranded Next default.

## Pandu (assistant) pattern — honesty is a hard rule

- **`PanduDock`** (`components/pandu/`): a compact icon-only pill (falcon eye, no text) →
  sea-glass card; suppressed via the shared `isShellSuppressedRoute` list. The pill is
  **draggable along the right edge** (pointer-captured, ≥6px = drag not click) and can be
  **tucked into a slim edge tab** (ChevronsRight in the card header hides; the edge tab
  restores) — both persisted in `store/pandu-store.ts` (`dockBottomOffset`, `dockCollapsed`),
  render gated behind `mounted` so SSR agrees. Free-text questions route through
  **`routePanduQuery`** (keyword → existing URL filters) — same router as the command palette.
- **Stub contract (jujur)**: nudges (`usePanduNudges`) are deterministic rules over queries that
  already exist — real numbers, rule-ranked, max 3, labeled "otomatis"; the card carries a
  permanent "Pratinjau" label; no generated prose, EVER, until the real AI lands. Dismissals
  persist per nudge-id (`store/pandu-store.ts`) and re-arm when the datum changes.

## Reuse these primitives — don't rebuild

- `components/ui/`: button card input textarea label select(native) switch popover calendar
  number-input badge skeleton table dialog alert-dialog dropdown-menu tooltip sheet separator
  tabs sonner avatar action-tooltip. Dialog/AlertDialog scroll internally (max-h dvh); close
  buttons are padded targets labeled "Tutup"; native Select uses `text-base md:text-sm` (iOS).
- `components/`: **PageHeader** (actions wrap) · **StatCard** (`num-display` value, `STAT_TONES`
  icon chip, optional `delta`) · **EmptyState** (optional `art` slot — BuoyArt for first-run
  empties, GullArt for positive-calm empties; filtered/search empties keep the plain icon) ·
  **ErrorState** (the error twin — icon + ID copy
  + "Coba lagi" wired to `refetch`; branch order is ALWAYS loading → error → empty → data; a
  failed query must NEVER render as "Belum ada…") · **StatusBadge** · **NumberDelta** ·
  **LowStockBadge** (Popover, warn tone — keyboard/touch reachable) · **DateRangePicker** (1
  month <sm + preset chips Hari ini/7 hari/30 hari/Bulan ini) · **TablePagination** ·
  **QrImage** (Skeleton loading + distinct failed state) + **QrCodeDialog** (prints ONE label through an
  isolated iframe — always a single centered page, not the in-page modal — with a Kecil/Sedang/Besar =
  30/50/70 mm size dropdown on Cetak; the labels-studio A4 sheet picks 1–4 columns, fewer = bigger) ·
  **VariantPickerDialog** · **ImageUploadPopover** · **BrandMark** · **WaveHairline** ·
  **maritime-art** · **error-screen** · charts: **ChartLegend** (every multi-series chart shows a
  visible legend — touch has no hover), chart wrappers carry `role="img"` + ID aria-label.
- `hooks/`: **useUrlFilters** · **useDebouncedValue** · **usePagination** · **useMediaQuery** ·
  **useReducedMotion** · **useSoundUnlock**/**useScanSoundPref** (per-station keys — a global
  sound pref needs deliberate design, don't fake one in settings).

## Patterns (copy these)

- **List filters**: `useUrlFilters` + 300ms debounced search; reset `page` to `'1'` on change;
  the component using `useSearchParams` must sit under `<Suspense>` (in-file boundary is fine —
  see `bundles-dashboard.tsx`); Suspense fallbacks are Skeleton blocks matching the page rhythm,
  NEVER `null`.
- **Mobile card-list pattern**: data tables keep the table for sm+ (`hidden sm:block`) and render
  stacked cards under sm (`sm:hidden`) with the SAME data + actions (share row-action renderers
  so they can't drift); touch targets ≥36px. Reference: `inventory-overview.tsx`,
  `products-dashboard.tsx`, `purchase-order-detail.tsx` (receive flow).
- **Table dress (ONE look everywhere)**: list tables sit bare in an
  `overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border` wrapper — NOT inside a Card — with default Table cell
  sizing (no per-surface big text/padding) and `TablePagination` below, outside the border
  (reference: `orders-dashboard.tsx`); detail-page item tables = a small count label
  (`Item · <span class=num>N</span>`) over the same bordered table (reference: `sale-detail.tsx`,
  `opname-detail.tsx`). Empty states render bare (no Card shell).
- **Sticky mobile action bar**: POS pins Total (`num-display`) + "Bayar" under sm; content gets
  `pb-24 sm:pb-0` clearance. Same recipe for any commit-action below the fold.
- **Forms** (RHF+zod): `FormLabel required`, iconed `FormDescription`, `NumberInput`; every
  Label has `htmlFor` to its input.
- **Row actions**: one primary button + a `⋯` DropdownMenu; icon-only actions get Tooltip +
  sr-only (NEVER bare `title=`). **Destructive confirms** (delete/cancel/reject/void) always go
  through an AlertDialog with destructive-styled action + consequence copy — no one-tap
  irreversibles.
- **Detail pages**: two columns (`lg:grid-cols-3`); header = eyebrow (section name) + title at
  PageHeader rhythm; loading skeletons MIRROR the real layout (no generic bars).
- **Toggles** `Switch`+`Label`; **dynamic inputs** live current→result previews; **colour
  variety** via `STAT_TONES`.
- **Wording**: user-facing copy is **Bahasa Indonesia** (informal "kamu"), sentence case; code
  stays English; no i18n framework. Canonical glossary as before plus: Bayar (checkout) ·
  payment labels via `paymentMethodLabel` (Tunai/QRIS/Transfer…) · "Rekam packing" (nav) ·
  "Laporan" (section) · "Fulfillment" badge label stays (user-approved) · sinkronisasi ·
  Terhubung/Terputus/Token kedaluwarsa · the phone-scan CTA is **"Scan dengan ponsel"** everywhere
  (POS/PO/opname/recordings) · "Opname stok" (nav) · "Tampilkan QR code" (row action). Dates/relative times go through `lib/formatters` (id-ID;
  date-fns `id` locale) — never `en-US` formatting.

## Shell & auth

- **`components/layout/nav-config.tsx` is the SINGLE source for shell navigation**: job-based
  sidebar groups (Jualan / Stok / Katalog / Kirim & retur / Laporan / Sistem — verbs over entity
  nouns; "Saran restok" + "Aktivitas stok" are first-class items, never nav-orphans again),
  `CREATE_ACTIONS` (the "Buat" menu AND the palette read it), `MOBILE_TABS`,
  `SHELL_SUPPRESSED_ROUTES`/`isShellSuppressedRoute` (tab bar + Pandu dock share it — never
  duplicate the list), `resolveActiveHref`/`resolveNavTitle`, and per-item `keywords` for the
  palette. Add a route → edit nav-config, everything else follows.
- **Ops-pulse badges**: `use-ops-pulse.ts` = live "needs my attention" counts composed from
  EXISTING module queries (PAID orders / PENDING returns via `meta.total` at pageSize 1; reorder
  `urgentCount` on the exact key Pandu warms). Nav rows render the count chip (suar amber ONLY
  for restock-urgent; neutral otherwise); the collapsed rail shows a dot + count in the Tooltip.
  Never invent a new endpoint for a badge.
- `components/layout/`: AppSidebar (icon rail w/ Tooltips, Create menu from CREATE_ACTIONS,
  brand tagline footer), DashboardNavbar (controlled mobile Sheet: scrolls + closes on navigate;
  theme toggle reads `resolvedTheme`; mobile center shows the page title via `resolveNavTitle`;
  **CommandPaletteTrigger** centered on md+, Search icon button on phones),
  SidebarNav (focus-visible rings, teal active edge-marker, "Rekam packing" ≠ "Rekaman"),
  **MobileTabBar** (5-slot bottom nav on phones, in normal flow, safe-area padding; Pesanan tab
  carries the ordersToShip pulse badge; the dock pill sits `bottom-20 md:bottom-4`), dashboard
  shell (`h-dvh`, skip-link "Langsung ke konten", `horizon-wash` main, `PanduDock` +
  `CommandPaletteProvider` mounted), `(dashboard)/template.tsx` = per-page ease-tide entrance
  (remounts on navigation; reduced-motion guard freezes it).
- **Auth enforced already** — don't touch config/middleware/cookies (HARD CONSTRAINT #2). The
  whole funnel (pages, panel, validators, AUTH_ERROR_MESSAGES, lockout) speaks ID. The auth
  brand panel shows a product vignette (mock queue on `bg-white/10`), not repeated feature copy.

## Command palette (Ctrl+K) — deterministic, honest

- **`components/command-palette.tsx`**: `CommandPaletteProvider` (global Ctrl/⌘+K, mounted once
  in DashboardShell) + `useCommandPalette()` + `CommandPaletteTrigger` (the navbar "search box"
  — sellers know search boxes; the kbd hint teaches the shortcut). Built on the ui/Dialog
  primitive, zero new deps. The affordances ADVERTISE the entity lookup — trigger copy
  "Cari menu, resi, SKU…", input placeholder "Cari menu, kode (S…/PO…), resi, atau SKU…" —
  don't water them back down to a generic "Cari…".
- Results = nav-config items + CREATE_ACTIONS filtered by token match over title/keywords; free
  text falls through **`routePanduQuery`** (same honest keyword router as the dock) labeled
  "Pandu · Pratinjau"; no match → `PANDU_SUGGESTIONS` chips. Every result is a REAL route —
  never a generated answer. Footer carries the kbd hints + the honesty line.
- **Entity jump** (`components/use-entity-jump.ts`): a code-looking query (no spaces, 3–64
  chars, not a menu word) resolves to real records under a "Lompat ke" group — S…/PO… via the
  full-list caches (shared query keys), OP… via the opname list `search` (hit verified
  client-side), ≥6 chars via orders by-resi, any code via the POS variant/bundle resolver
  (variant → inventory `?search=<sku>`; the resolver has no productId). Lookups are
  enabled-gated + debounced; in-flight shows a muted "Mencari kode…" row.
- **Scan-wedge**: CommandPaletteProvider buffers document keydowns (<50ms inter-key gap); a
  ≥6-char burst ending in Enter, when focus is NOT in an editable element and the route is not
  shell-suppressed, opens the palette pre-filled with the code — a USB scan gun navigates the
  app with zero pairing. Only the triggering Enter is swallowed.
- The dashboard-home hero NL bar was retired in favor of this (the dock keeps its own input);
  don't reintroduce per-page ask-bars.

## Dashboard home = briefing, not a stat wall

- Order on home: greeting → **`Briefing`** ("Antrian kerja · otomatis", app-layer composition in
  `app/(dashboard)/dashboard/briefing.tsx`) → "Pintasan" quick actions → WaveHairline →
  InventoryDashboard. The briefing's queue rows (oversold → restock-urgent → PAID-unshipped →
  PENDING returns) deep-link to pre-filtered lists (`?status=PAID`, `?status=PENDING`) and exist
  ONLY when count > 0; all-clear renders the calm "Laut tenang" row. Branch order is loading →
  all-failed ErrorState → all-clear → rows; a partially-failed source shows the muted "Sebagian
  antrian gagal dimuat — Coba lagi" line, NEVER a silent zero.

## Daily-ops patterns (shipped — reuse, don't rebuild)

- **Peek panel** (`modules/orders/components/order-peek.tsx`): list rows open a READ-ONLY right
  Sheet (`sm:max-w-md`) — meta rows, compact items, packing-video link, "Buka halaman penuh";
  mutations stay on the full page. Rows are keyboard-actionable (tabIndex + Enter/Space guarded
  by `event.target === event.currentTarget`); inner links `stopPropagation`. Copy this shape for
  other triage lists (returns next).
- **Days-of-cover gauge** (`modules/inventory/components/days-cover-gauge.tsx`): thin depletion
  bar colored URGENT→signed-down / SOON→highlight / else status-ok, fed by the reorder report
  joined client-side (same query key Pandu warms); it's an ENHANCEMENT — the table never blocks
  on it. Row action "Buat PO" → `/dashboard/purchasing/new?variant=<id>` (PoForm appends that
  line from its reorder report, ref-guarded one-shot).
- **POS ergonomics**: quick-tender row (Uang pas + 3 smallest covering notes) feeds the
  kembalian calculator; `pos-favorites.store.ts` (ids only, capped 12) pins variants/bundles to
  a "Favorit" strip shown when search is empty; desktop shortcuts `/` (focus search) and `F8`
  (jump to pay) with kbd hint chips. Don't add more shortcuts ad hoc.
- **Tutup hari** (`app/(dashboard)/dashboard/tutup-hari-dialog.tsx`): end-of-day dialog —
  today-vs-yesterday from the profit report (queries mount only while open), carried-over work
  rows, and a PLAIN-TEXT WhatsApp recap (`wa.me/?text=`) + copy button. No invented metrics; the
  footer credits the profit report. No streaks/gamification — the recap IS the reward.
- **Papan keberangkatan** (`/dashboard/orders/board`): a packing-station status board — PAID
  rows ("Terekam — siap kirim" when `fulfilledAt`, else "Menunggu dikemas") then recent SHIPPED
  ("Dikirim"), in the STANDARD table dress (default cell sizing, sentence-case StatusBadge — the
  board is NOT special-cased big), `num` on resi/counts, live clock, the shared ghost back
  button, 20s polling via `useOrdersBoardQuery` (NO socket, NO flip animation); route lives in
  `SHELL_SUPPRESSED_ROUTES`.

## Landing & marketing surfaces

- **Show the product, not stock art**: landing/auth visuals are composed from the REAL
  design-system primitives (`components/marketing/product-mocks.tsx` — AnjunganMock, ledger
  trail, dispute-evidence, POS total, profit rows). Mocks are `aria-hidden` and ALWAYS paired
  with an sr-only Indonesian summary. Plausible generic demo data only.
- **Honesty is the marketing**: no invented testimonials, user counts, pricing, or logos; the
  proof sections are the append-only ledger trail + the packing-video dispute story ("Bukti,
  bukan klaim"). Pandu stays an honest "Segera hadir" teaser — zero fake interactivity.

## Gotchas

- Never `next build` while the dev server runs (shared `.next`). Build BEFORE typecheck after
  adding routes/changing page props (typed routes regenerate in `.next/types`).
- `useSearchParams` (incl. via `useUrlFilters`) needs a `<Suspense>` boundary or the build fails.
- Typed routes: computed hrefs need `as Route`.
- PowerShell commits: never put double quotes inside `git commit -m` here-strings (PS 5.1
  re-quoting splits the args).
- Deps for this system: `geist`, `@fontsource-variable/plus-jakarta-sans`, `react-day-picker`,
  `@radix-ui/react-popover`, `@radix-ui/react-switch`, `zustand` (persist for Pandu dismissals).
